-- Bangkok Airways sets IPO price at 25 baht/share -sources
-- By Manunphattr Dhanananphorn
-- Fri Oct 17, 2014 09:58PM EDT
-- None



BANGKOK, Oct 18 (Reuters) - Thai full-service carrier Bangkok Airways Co Ltd has priced its initial public offering (IPO) at 25 baht (0.77 U.S. cents) per share, as it raises 13 billion baht ($401 million) to fund expansion, people with knowledge of the matter said on Saturday.

The IPO price was in the middle of the range of 23 and 27 baht, the sources, who declined to be identified, told Reuters.  Bangkok Airways, which describes itself as a "boutique airline", plans to sell 520 million new shares, or a stake of 24.8 percent.